    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Digital distortion that occurs when a sampling frequency is too low, as in jagged stair-stepping in curved lines or transitions in images. In sound, aliasing occurs when the sampling rate drops below 40 kilohertz (Khz).</Note_Text>
